<br>
Being that you're only 7 levels away from being trivial, I would start by obtaining the items for Shovel of Ponz and Broom of Trilon, since you'll need them to complete your epic, if you ever decide to go that route.<br>
<br>
If by then, you think that you'll find use of the other focus items, then by all means, complete the Torch of Alna and Stein of Ulissa quests. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1515<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 12:26:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=507.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where is the specific info on Pet Focus items?</span><hr size=1> I found the 49 Fire pet occasionally useful, and until I got my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velious Mage Bracer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the torch was the item I carried around for reclaim energy.<br>
